For XML 1.0, another [StackOverflow answer][1] recommends using something like this:

```java
// Regex matches illegal XML 1.0 characters
String xml10pattern = &quot;[^\u0009\u0020-\uD7FF\uE000-\uFFFD\ud800\udc00-\udbff\udfff\r\n]&quot;;

String badXmlData = &quot;\u0011 YOUR XML STRING HERE&quot;;

// Replace all the matching (illegal) characters with the empty string, removing them
