As the RequestMapping enbales the creation of multiple functions to deal with the different RequestParams. I was able to redefine the original `index` function to only deal with a placeholder param as follows

```java
    @Deprecated
    @GetMapping(params = {&quot;deprecated&quot;})
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.OK)
    @Override
    public List&lt;ItemResponse&gt; index() {
        return super.index();
    }
```
In this way I can use the default mapping as I need
```java
    @GetMapping
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.OK)
    public List&lt;ItemResponse&gt; index(...params) {
        return service.index(departmentId);
    }
```
It does not remove the old implementation completely but it constraints it to the use of the param `deprecated` which can actually be useful

